{{Infobox award | name = Michigan Emmy Award | image = | imagesize = | caption = Michigan Emmy Award | description = Excellence in [[television]] | presenter = [[National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences|NATAS]] | State = [[Southfield, Michigan]] | year = 1980 | website = http://www.natasmichigan.org/ }}
The '''Michigan Emmy Awards''' is a chapter of the [[National Academy of Television Arts & Sciences]] (MI-NATAS) The [[Southfield, Michigan]] division was founded in 1980. In addition to granting the Michigan [[Emmy Awards]], this division awards scholarships, honors industry veterans at the Silver Circle Celebration, conducts National Student Television Awards of Excellence, has a free research and a nationwide job bank. The chapter also participates in judging Emmy entries at the regional and national levels.<ref name="urlNATAS Michigan">{{cite web |url=http://www.natasmichigan.org/ |title=NATAS Michigan |author= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |format= |work= |publisher=[[NATAS]] |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= |accessdate=2010-07-06}}The Michigan Emmy Awards</ref><ref name="urlThe Jim McKay Scholarship - The Emmy Awards">{{cite web |url=http://www.emmyonline.tv/scholarship/ |title=The Jim McKay Scholarship - The Emmy Awards |author=[[NATAS]] |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= |accessdate=2010-07-06}}Jim McKay Scholarship</ref>
==Board of governors==
The Board of Governors is a working board, which works together collaboratively to ensure they are providing for the best interests of the membership.<ref name="urlNATAS Michigan : Contact Us">{{cite web |url=http://www.natasmichigan.org/contact.html |title=NATAS Michigan : Contact Us |author=[[NATAS]] |authorlink= |coauthors= |date= |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= |accessdate=2010-07-06}}Board of Governers</ref>
